WEBVTT

00:35.160 --> 00:37.662
Why did you come in
         so late last night?

00:37.704 --> 00:39.497
Me and Chance
       were just catching up.

00:39.539 --> 00:41.499
Please tell me
    you read everybody's script.

00:41.541 --> 00:43.043
Look, I'm sorry.
          Things got crazy.

00:43.084 --> 00:45.503
I promise,
       next week, I got y'all.

00:45.545 --> 00:47.005
It's a questionnaire
          that requires you

00:47.047 --> 00:49.841
to look at your partner
       and your relationship.

00:49.883 --> 00:51.509
Enjoying your new life
           as an actress?

00:51.551 --> 00:53.720
Ah, well, I still have
      to teach yoga part-time.

00:53.762 --> 00:55.805
You wanna grab a drink
              sometime?

00:55.847 --> 00:57.515
I feel like every time I try

00:57.557 --> 00:58.933
to do something nice,
         you have an issue.

00:58.975 --> 01:02.979
We're experiencing
   two very different Hollywoods.

01:03.021 --> 01:04.522
I'm bisexual.

01:11.112 --> 01:13.198
All right.
   I think we should get started.

01:13.239 --> 01:14.157
Hattie, you're up.

01:14.199 --> 01:16.284
-So y'all ready for my notes?
          -Mm-hmm.

01:16.326 --> 01:17.869
Okay, I wrote 'em down.

01:17.911 --> 01:20.205
-All right.
               -Okay.

01:20.246 --> 01:24.084
Jackson, I thought your script
       was a really cool idea,

01:24.125 --> 01:28.129
but that last act
         needs so much work.

01:29.672 --> 01:30.799
I'm aware.

01:30.840 --> 01:33.176
And all the women
       are sounding the same.

01:33.218 --> 01:35.845
I mean, you gotta give me
         some variety, bro.

01:35.887 --> 01:38.389
And why did you have the dad
      kill his boss like that?

01:38.431 --> 01:41.059
I mean, he could have gave him
    a warning or something first.

01:41.101 --> 01:45.230
It just came out of nowhere,
   and honestly, I didn't buy it.

01:45.271 --> 01:48.316
Tisha. Tisha, Tisha, Tisha.

01:48.358 --> 01:51.611
-You got skills, okay?
                -Hey!

01:51.653 --> 01:54.322
But I could not stand
       your damn protagonist.

01:54.364 --> 01:55.573
She reminded me of this girl

01:55.615 --> 01:56.783
that I used to date
           back in the day

01:56.825 --> 02:00.078
that was always sucking
      her teeth for no reason.

02:00.120 --> 02:02.789
And it also seemed like she was
     always mad about something

02:02.831 --> 02:04.582
and I just didn't know what,
              you know?

02:04.624 --> 02:08.336
Damn, can you just be nice
            for a second?

02:08.378 --> 02:13.299
And, I don't know, it feels
       very angry Black woman.

02:13.341 --> 02:16.678
And I know we trying
    to get away from that trope.

02:16.719 --> 02:19.389
-Let that go.
              -Uh-huh.

02:19.430 --> 02:22.350
Idina, my girl,

02:22.392 --> 02:24.894
your script was so relatable.

02:24.936 --> 02:26.855
Like, I could really
        see myself in Robbie.

02:26.896 --> 02:29.566
I mean, she was hilarious,
        a bit of a hot mess,

02:29.607 --> 02:30.567
but I liked her.

02:30.608 --> 02:32.402
The only thing
         I didn't understand

02:32.443 --> 02:34.779
was why Isabelle
      was so into her, though.

02:34.821 --> 02:37.073
Like, Izzy had a great life.

02:37.115 --> 02:40.577
She's got the fly store.
      She's got the cool whip.

02:40.618 --> 02:42.996
She's obviously a great cook.

02:43.037 --> 02:45.707
Why is she following
     behind this dusty-ass girl?

02:45.748 --> 02:48.334
I don't know,
      I guess I'm just not here

02:48.376 --> 02:52.881
for the unrequited
    lesbian love story right now.

02:52.922 --> 02:56.467
Maybe 'cause I've been through
      that shit too many times.

02:56.509 --> 02:58.219
And the truth is,

02:58.261 --> 03:01.097
these characters are just
     a little too happy for me.

03:01.139 --> 03:02.807
I mean, I've been
         through that shit.

03:02.849 --> 03:05.518
Ain't nothing happy about it.

03:05.560 --> 03:08.813
And to be real with you,

03:08.855 --> 03:11.357
at one point, I just wished
       they would just move on

03:11.399 --> 03:15.236
and go their separate ways, but
   then you wouldn't have a show,

03:15.278 --> 03:17.322
so never mind.

03:17.363 --> 03:21.910
All right, thank you, Hattie,
     for being overly prepared.

03:21.951 --> 03:23.828
Oh, yeah, I told you
   I was gon' come prepared today.

03:23.870 --> 03:27.290
-Mm.
    -Yeah, I ain't come to play.

03:27.332 --> 03:29.876
So how did I do?

03:29.918 --> 03:32.170
Uh, you did great.

03:32.212 --> 03:34.714
Just next time,
    you don't have to go so hard.

03:34.756 --> 03:35.757
When we say first brush,

03:35.798 --> 03:37.717
we just want
       your general thoughts,

03:37.759 --> 03:39.677
not everything
         you hated about it.

03:39.719 --> 03:41.971
Oh, my bad.

03:42.013 --> 03:44.474
See, I ain't used
       to being around people.

03:44.515 --> 03:45.642
Well, if you wanna get staffed,

03:45.683 --> 03:47.602
you're gonna have
         to get used to it.

03:47.644 --> 03:48.811
You right.

03:48.853 --> 03:51.773
But honestly, I think
     you'll be great in a room.

03:51.814 --> 03:53.024
I'm pretty sure
         you're gonna get on

03:53.066 --> 03:54.567
most of the people's nerves...

03:56.236 --> 03:58.738
But you'll keep
          everybody awake.

03:58.780 --> 04:00.531
Well, I'll take that.

04:02.575 --> 04:06.663
So you really
     didn't like my script, huh?

04:06.704 --> 04:07.872
Nah, I liked it,

04:07.914 --> 04:09.999
and it was really nice
   to read somebody else's script

04:10.041 --> 04:12.502
instead of just
     staring at my own all day.

04:12.543 --> 04:14.379
-Yeah, I feel the same way.
              -Mm-hmm.

04:14.420 --> 04:16.714
And it also reminds me
    I'm not the only one out here

04:16.756 --> 04:18.883
struggling to get words
            on the page.

04:18.925 --> 04:20.343
Yeah.

04:20.385 --> 04:21.970
Thank you, Idina.

04:22.011 --> 04:24.472
Being a part of this group
        has been really nice.

04:24.514 --> 04:27.058
It's been really nice
             having you.

04:31.062 --> 04:35.316
Hey, would you wanna
       go catch a movie, or--

04:35.358 --> 04:37.068
Oh, shit.

04:37.110 --> 04:38.736
Is everything okay?

04:38.778 --> 04:40.905
Marie's calling
        an emergency meeting.

04:40.947 --> 04:42.240
What's the emergency?

04:42.282 --> 04:44.784
I don't know, but it must be
          something serious

04:44.826 --> 04:47.161
'cause she ain't called
      one of these in a minute.

04:47.203 --> 04:49.247
Look, I'ma go figure out
          what's going on.

04:49.289 --> 04:52.333
-I'll catch you later?
        -Okay, cool.

04:52.375 --> 04:54.460
And you need to bring snacks
             next time.

04:54.502 --> 04:55.378
I got you.

04:55.420 --> 04:57.880
I'ma bring some barbeque
        pork rinds next time.

04:57.922 --> 05:00.758
What? Don't nobody eat those.

05:00.800 --> 05:04.554
upbeat piano music

05:09.559 --> 05:11.185
Chuck is bi?!

05:11.227 --> 05:14.147
You know, technically,
    this ain't a real emergency,

05:14.188 --> 05:15.273
right, because
        I already knew that.

05:15.315 --> 05:18.526
But I'm just glad
     that he's owning his truth.

05:18.568 --> 05:19.861
I need to process this.

05:19.902 --> 05:21.863
-Have you processed this?
            -Yes, I have.

05:21.904 --> 05:23.448
Probably 'cause
      you already knew, right?

05:23.489 --> 05:26.701
Hattie, if he didn't come out
    to you, you're just assuming.

05:26.743 --> 05:28.703
Girl, I know my people.

05:28.745 --> 05:30.121
Then why didn't you
          tell me about it?

05:30.163 --> 05:32.623
Because I couldn't tell you
    that I think your man is gay.

05:32.665 --> 05:33.833
Well, he's not.

05:33.875 --> 05:36.336
You right. He's bi.

05:36.377 --> 05:38.212
So what are we doing
             about this?

05:38.254 --> 05:41.466
We're not doing anything.
   We're still gonna be together.

05:41.507 --> 05:43.051
And that's not abnormal.

05:43.092 --> 05:46.012
I know a lot of straight dudes
         that date bi girls

05:46.054 --> 05:48.014
and a lot of bi dudes
      that date straight girls.

05:48.056 --> 05:50.224
And, you know,
      that's just how it goes.

05:50.266 --> 05:52.018
It's okay.

05:52.060 --> 05:53.770
So you guys are okay?

05:53.811 --> 05:55.271
Yeah, we're fine.

05:55.313 --> 05:57.815
And he's cool with you
      telling us that he's bi?

05:57.857 --> 06:00.068
I asked for his permission
             last night.

06:00.109 --> 06:01.986
How forward-thinking of you.

06:02.028 --> 06:04.405
I just wanted you both to know.

06:04.447 --> 06:07.075
I'm still digesting.

06:07.116 --> 06:08.910
I've digested.

06:08.951 --> 06:11.329
Me and Ben hung out
          the other night.

06:11.371 --> 06:12.038
Why?

06:12.080 --> 06:14.165
He asked me
      to have drinks with him.

06:14.207 --> 06:16.417
-Mm-mm.
         -He's not that bad.

06:16.459 --> 06:19.128
Well, he's definitely
       ready to leave Lauren.

06:19.170 --> 06:21.005
He just wants a Black trophy
             on his arm.

06:21.047 --> 06:23.674
Do not fall for his bullshit.

06:23.716 --> 06:26.260
Oh, shit. I gotta take this.

06:26.302 --> 06:27.929
Don't tell anyone else
            about Chuck.

06:27.970 --> 06:31.265
-We got you.
                -Duh.

06:31.307 --> 06:32.725
-Bye.
            -Bye.

06:32.767 --> 06:34.018
Hello?

06:34.060 --> 06:36.854
I'm still in shock, by the way.

06:36.896 --> 06:38.815
I don't know why.

06:38.856 --> 06:42.443
When are you gonna tell Marie
         about you and Ida?

06:42.485 --> 06:43.361
I don't know.

06:43.403 --> 06:46.406
Whenever I know
        what the hell we are.

06:46.447 --> 06:47.865
upbeat music

06:47.907 --> 06:49.867
I emailed you the proposal.

06:49.909 --> 06:50.952
Did you get it?

06:50.993 --> 06:53.704
I did, and I got
       some questions for you.

06:53.746 --> 06:55.706
Okay.

06:55.748 --> 06:56.958
Why do we need Monument?

06:56.999 --> 06:58.918
Why do we need
      any of these white folks?

06:58.960 --> 07:01.379
Because historical dramas
             cost money.

07:01.421 --> 07:04.340
-I got money.
    -Not enough to pay for this.

07:04.382 --> 07:06.634
I know people
      with more money than me.

07:06.676 --> 07:07.844
It isn't just about the money.

07:07.885 --> 07:10.721
You need infrastructure,
            distribution,

07:10.763 --> 07:12.849
someone to take care
        of all the paperwork.

07:12.890 --> 07:14.851
We can get people
         to do all of that.

07:14.892 --> 07:17.353
Look, I've been hustling
           my whole life.

07:17.395 --> 07:21.023
If I get to the pros,
      I can make a damn movie.

07:21.065 --> 07:23.401
Those are two
       very different things.

07:23.443 --> 07:24.318
I get it.

07:24.360 --> 07:27.822
You're not here for it
     right now, and that's okay.

07:27.864 --> 07:29.615
I'ma keep working on you.

07:29.657 --> 07:31.284
Then we gon' get there.

07:31.325 --> 07:34.370
Okay, well, in the meantime,
       can we talk directors?

07:34.412 --> 07:35.872
We can talk Black directors.

07:35.913 --> 07:37.915
Perfect, because
    that's all I have to present.

07:37.957 --> 07:40.376
Wonderful.
    That's all I wanted to hear.

07:45.882 --> 07:48.259
Why are you so happy?

07:48.301 --> 07:51.304
'Cause I finally found
        my writer community,

07:51.345 --> 07:54.682
and 'cause I'm finally
         not scared of you.

07:56.017 --> 07:57.852
Am I really that scary?

07:57.894 --> 07:58.936
Yes.

07:58.978 --> 08:00.396
I'm just blunt.

08:00.438 --> 08:03.274
And you can be
         a little cold too.

08:03.316 --> 08:04.400
Ida B.!

08:04.442 --> 08:06.360
-Hey.
      -So glad to run into you.

08:06.402 --> 08:08.863
Uh, what a surprise
          to see you here.

08:08.905 --> 08:10.072
I am loving the new season

08:10.114 --> 08:11.532
of "Cocoa's Butter,"
             by the way.

08:11.574 --> 08:13.284
Oh, thank you.

08:15.661 --> 08:17.747
Oh, this is Hattie.

08:17.788 --> 08:21.125
She is an amazing young writer.

08:21.167 --> 08:22.418
Look at you,

08:22.460 --> 08:24.337
always mentoring
        the next generation.

08:24.378 --> 08:26.130
Yeah, that's Ida B., all right,

08:26.172 --> 08:29.509
always reaching back while
   climbing the corporate ladder.

08:29.550 --> 08:31.177
Hattie, pay close attention.

08:31.219 --> 08:33.304
You've got a lot to learn
        from this smart lady.

08:33.346 --> 08:35.014
Oh, I'm taking notes.

08:35.056 --> 08:37.808
-She's adorable.
            -Yes, she is.

08:43.940 --> 08:45.691
Do you ladies need
           anything else?

08:45.733 --> 08:47.318
-Just the check.
              -Hattie.

08:47.360 --> 08:49.195
I'll pay for my shit.
       You can pay for yours.

08:49.237 --> 08:52.323
-Hattie--
      -I'll come back in a bit.

08:52.365 --> 08:55.368
You know, man, I don't know
   why I keep giving you chances.

08:55.409 --> 08:57.954
What was I supposed to do?
   Introduce you as my girlfriend?

08:57.995 --> 09:00.748
You could have at least
    introduced me as your friend.

09:00.790 --> 09:02.750
I would have taken that.

09:02.792 --> 09:05.211
I thought you were taking care
      of your half of the bill.

09:05.253 --> 09:07.004
I'll Cash App you.

09:24.730 --> 09:26.357
-Hey.
                -Hey.

09:28.359 --> 09:30.987
Don't be scared.
          Take your moment.

09:31.028 --> 09:32.154
I don't know.

09:32.196 --> 09:33.906
It feels weird
      to walk down a red carpet

09:33.948 --> 09:35.449
if nobody knows who I am.

09:35.491 --> 09:37.535
Random people walk red carpets
            all the time.

09:37.577 --> 09:39.954
I know; I don't wanna be
        one of those people.

09:39.996 --> 09:41.455
If you keep killing it
          on social media,

09:41.497 --> 09:43.082
you'll be
    the most famous person here.

09:43.124 --> 09:44.875
